    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can try this to avoid indicating custom date and if there is need to display start and end dates of current month:</p>\n\n<pre><code>    LocalDate start = LocalDate.now().minusDays(LocalDate.now().getDayOfMonth()-1);\n    LocalDate end = LocalDate.now().minusDays(LocalDate.now().getDayOfMonth()).plusMonths(1);\n    System.out.println(\"Start of month: \" + start);\n    System.out.println(\"End of month: \" + end);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><em>Result:</em></p>\n\n<pre><code>&gt;     Start of month: 2019-12-01\n&gt;     End of month: 2019-12-30\n</code></pre>\n"
